# Overview

picc is a linker for PIC microcontrollers' code objects in the COFF format.

# Building and Installing picc

To install picc, just execute the command:

    python setup.py install

# Usage

picc
----
To link several code objects, just type the following command:

picc object1.o object2.o object3.o

That will generate the file a.hex, with the linked code. If you want to give
a name to the output hex file use the -o option:

picc object1.o object2.o object3.o -o program.hex

picc-objdump
------------
To inspect the contents of an object file, type:

picc-objdump object.o

